Police have arrested three men and have widened the search for three more following separate cases in the province. CAPE TOWN - Police have arrested three men and have widened the search for three more, following two separate gang shootings in the Eastern Cape.Sean Tarentaal was killed in front of his house in Port Elizabeth over the weekend.The police's Priscilla Naidu says his killers are still at large. Mr Tarentaal sustained a fatal gunshot wound to his chest. The deceased has no gang affiliations and the suspects are unknown at this stage. Naidu adds they re investigating a case of murder.In a separate incident, three men have been charged with attempted murder.It s understood they forced their way into a Jeffreys Bay home and opened fire on residents.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)